  "bindingSections": {
    "scope-isolation": {
      "description": "Scope-resolved object identity (kernel spec §2.3, docs/KrakenKernelSpecification.md#23-hash). A Scope is a host-bound partition identity supplied at backend/connection construction; the kernel syscall surface stays scope-free. Hash resolution to durable storage is confined to the constructing Scope, so identical content under two Scopes is two independent durable objects and store.has / store.get / enumeration can never observe content outside the constructing Scope. The cross-scope isolation conformance contract for this surface lives at boundaries/kernel/conformance/plans/kernel-scope-isolation.json (capability kernel.scope-isolation). KRT-BE001 declares the surface and the conformance-plan reference; KRT-BE007 promotes the plan to runnable, registered, evidence-backed conformance once memory/SQLite/PostgreSQL realize the scope binding (KRT-BE003 through KRT-BE006)."
    }
  },
